Message: Welcome!
how to I integrate API?

To integrate the API, you'll want to follow these steps: 1. Create an Ad Account in our Ad Manager. 2. Request your token by clicking 'Help' on the left side of your screen or emailing adsupport@newsbreak.com with your Organization ID. 3. Once you have your token, you can start making API calls. If you run into any issues, feel free to reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for help!
do we support clickflare?

Yes, we do support Clickflare! You can integrate a NewsBreak Postback with Clickflare by following the specific setup instructions in our help center. If you need more details or assistance, just let me know!
can I talk to a live agent

I totally understand wanting to chat with a live agent! Unfortunately, I can't connect you directly to one. However, I can help you with your questions or issues right here. What do you need assistance with?

how do I test new creatives?

To test new creatives, you can follow these steps: 
1. Choose a tracking platform (like RedTrack or Voluum) to monitor your campaigns. 
2. Set up your creatives within the platform and ensure they are properly configured. 
3. Launch a small-scale test campaign to gather data on performance. 
4. Analyze the results to see which creatives perform best.
If you need more specific guidance based on the platform you're using, let me know!

how do i set up tracking

To set up tracking with RedTrack, you'll need to follow these steps: 1. Log in to your RedTrack account and click on 'Traffic channels.' 2. Click '+ NEW FROM TEMPLATE' and search for NewsBreak. 3. Once you click 'Add,' the NewsBreak Template should open up with the fields populated. Make sure to fill in the necessary details, including the s2s URL provided in the template. You can find detailed instructions in this article: [How to set up a RedTrack Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/25515090832013-How-to-set-up-a-RedTrack-Postback-on-NewsBreak). If you have any specific questions while setting it up, feel free to ask!
